#Encapsulation : Wrapping  data(variable) + method (function) into single unit 
#and restricting direct acceass to the data

#you don't directly touch internal data - you use the controlled method 


class Student:
  def __init__(self):
    self.__marks=0

  def set_marks(self,mark):
    if mark>0:
      self.__marks=mark

  def get_marks(self):
    return self.__marks

  
s=Student()
s.set_marks(90)
print(s.get_marks())


Encapsulation is the process of binding the data and method together into single unit

-encapsulation is the piller of oops


what is inheritence Inheritence: one class is using the properties and method of other class

